In May 2014, flok announced a self-service loyalty platform for SMBs to build their own programs with beacon integration. At that time, approximately 40,000 businesses were using the service.<ref>http://www.mediapost.com/publications/article/225373/loyalblocks-adds-beacon-to-self-serve-loyalty-plat.html</ref> In 2016, flok released a turnkey chatbot service for local businesses,<ref>https://venturebeat.com/2016/07/26/flok-uses-bluetooth-and-chatbots-to-lure-people-inside-thousands-of-small-businesses/</ref><ref>http://marketingland.com/flok-wants-bring-chatbots-small-business-masses-186056</ref> and was featured in [[AdWeek]] for developing the first "weed bot" chatbot for a [[California]] [[cannabis]] business.<ref>{{cite web|title=This California Marijuana Dispensary Is Using Bots to Understand Customers' Preferences|url=http://www.adweek.com/news/technology/california-marijuana-dispensary-using-bots-understand-customers-preferences-172238|publisher=[[Adweek]]|accessdate=26 July 2016}}</ref>
