'''Inframat Corporation''' is a nanotechnology company founded in 1996 with headquarters and a pilot plant / R&D facility in Manchester, CT. Product focus is in the areas of (i) medical and industrial nanocoatings, (ii) high surface area nanofibrous media for water treatment, and (iii) magnetic nanocomposites. Inframat has pioneered the [[Solution plasma spray]] (“SPS”) process, based on the substitution of solution for powder feedstocks in [[thermal spray]] systems. Inframat’s Advanced Materials subsidiary sells a variety of commercial materials to large companies and research institutions.
